Job Descriptions:
The Company
B2Gold is an international senior gold producer headquartered in Vancouver, Canada. The Company currently has three operating gold mines and numerous exploration and development projects in various countries including Mali, Namibia, Colombia and the Philippines.
Position
Regional CSR Manager, West Africa (Mali)
Introduction
The Regional CSR Manager will fulfill the corporate social responsibility mandate for B2Gold at the project level in West Africa with the aim to build strong support and consent for the development of future mine projects while driving positive long-term outcomes for local communities near B2Gold’s Fekola Mine in Mali. The position will manage multi-stakeholder engagement and relations, socio-economic impact management and community development, related strategic partnerships, and social management plans at B2Gold’s development projects. The position must also collaborate with and support the Fekola Mine Community Relations Department and function. The position will also develop and manage the implementation of significant regional community development projects.
The Regional CSR Manager will be a self-directed professional with excellent project management skills and who is comfortable working across multiple disciplines in a remote and fast-paced environment where there is frequent change.
Location and Reporting Manager
The position will report to the Development Project Manager on day-to-day operational and administrative matters, will support the regional Exploration Manager and the Fekola Mine General Manager where relevant, and report to the B2Gold Corporate CSR Manager on strategic and technical matters. This position will be based at B2Gold’s Fekola Mine in Mali, Africa on an 8/4 fly in-fly out rotation schedule. Regional travel will be required.
Duties and Responsibilities
Fulfill the Corporate CSR mandate at the project level with regards to B2Gold’s CSR policies, standards and commitments;
Manage a Regional Community Relations Department, including hiring, development and management of staff, consultants, and contractors;
Support project permitting efforts including:
Ensuring the completion of socio-economic baseline and impact assessment, and management plan development, for project ESIA & ESMP,
Directing processes for land acquisition and physical and/or economic displacement, including asset survey and inventory, delivery of compensation frameworks, and resettlement planning and execution.
Identify, analyze, and manage project risks related to social impacts. Develop and manage relevant CSR strategies and action/management plans related to social issues such as:
stakeholder engagement
grievance and conflict management
community development and investment,
local employment and local procurement
land acquisition and resettlement
artisanal and small-scale mining
indigenous peoples and cultural heritage
human rights
social closure planning
Manage data and information and monitor social performance metrics and indicators;
Oversee the Social Impact Management System at project level;
Oversee Departmental reporting including routine project reporting and monthly, quarterly, and annual reports and presentations to Corporate management, as required;
Collaborate as needed with the Fekola Mine (i.e., General Manager, Community Relations and other relevant Departments) and the B2Gold Bamako office representatives to support relevant B2Gold activities and objectives;
Travel to current and future operations and projects of B2Gold, as required;
Execute training and capacity building for CSR skills and strategy as required;
Prepare and manage CSR budgets and schedules at project level;
Maintain current on industry best practice and international performance standards related to social issues; and
Perform other duties as required in support of Company objectives.
Requirements
Degree in International Development, Social Science, or a relevant field;
At least 10 years of relevant experience, with 3 years in a management role level;
International working experience;
Experience in the mining industry or extractive sector;
Experience in managing internal teams and consultants, directly;
Strong knowledge, expertise, and understanding of the application and implementation of IFC Performance Standards and related international standards;
Demonstrated ability to scale and apply strategies to local environments and different cultures;
Excellent communication and collaboration abilities with all levels of internal and external stakeholders;
Ability to work with minimum supervision and manage multiple demands;
Knowledge and experience working with Microsoft software (Word, Outlook, Excel, Project); and
Strong English and French written, verbal and presentation skills, required.
Only applications submitted in English will be reviewed.
Compensation
B2Gold offers a competitive compensation package, including salary to commensurate with experience, knowledge and skills, plus a comprehensive group benefits package for employee and their dependents.
Other
B2Gold requires employees to be fully vaccinated (and maintain fully vaccinated status), subject to applicable human-rights related exemptions and availability in candidate's home country.
We thank all applicants for their interest in B2Gold Corp; however only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.
B2Gold prioritizes local employment, supports empowerment initiatives and continuously works towards a people profile that matches the demographics of the respective national settings in which we operate, while appreciating our inclusive culture that attracts talent from around the world. As an equal opportunity employer, B2Gold values diversity and we encourage all qualified candidates to apply.

Work Type : Full Time
Location : QLD
Permanent opportunity with great career prospects
Develop skills working closely with an established analytics team
Toowong location, Brisbane Inner City
About us
At Auto & General (A&G), we provide smarter products and solutions to safeguard our customers in their time of need. Our range of general insurance products protect customers on the road, at home and on holiday with various Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents, and Pet Insurance products as well as Roadside Assistance.

Our culture of ‘high performance with high integrity’ underpins our values and the way we interact with our customers, the community and each other. We’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.

Visit our website to find out more.

The Role:

We are seeking a Senior Portfolio Insights Analyst to join our high performing Pricing Team. The purpose of this role will be to assist the Portfolio Monitoring Manager to enhance the monitoring capabilities and produce analytical insights. This position will be well suited to someone who likes a fast-paced environment with opportunities to work in a wide range of areas.

Accountabilities:
Building monitoring dashboards to enable early detection of emerging issues and to provide visibility on business performance;
Building machine learning capabilities such as anomaly detection models into the monitoring suite;
Maintaining, migrating and enhancing the reporting suite aimed at supporting Senior Management to effectively manage the relevant insurance portfolios;
Identifying, reporting and analysing trends in the Domestic insurance portfolios, including e.g. volume, premium and profitability related indicators;
Performing analytical investigations to generate actionable insights for Senior Management to make informed decisions;
Working closely with the product owners and the wider business to develop effective measures to address emerging trends;
Analysing and segmenting transactional data from the proprietary underwriting system(s) and policy database;
Supporting the business with their quantitative analysis needs, e.g. review of underwriting question sets and processes;
Driving continuous improvement of data quality, presentation, and insight generation, including embedding relevant metrics in regular reporting;
Monitoring and reporting on the progress of pricing and product changes;
Performing other relevant activities as requested from time to time to meet operational requirements.


Qualifications, Experience and Skills
Bachelor’s degree in Mathematics, Economics, Data Science, Actuarial Science, Information Management or Statistics or related field;
A superior problem-solving ability with excellent attention to detail and accuracy;
Ability to communicate effectively across all levels of the organisation;
Proven experience in data analysis, including ability to:
Work with large data from various sources through various platforms;
Access and manipulate data quickly and efficiently;
Work with both structured and unstructured datasets.
Previous experience within General Insurance is highly advantageous;
Working knowledge and understanding of short-tail insurance product(s), underwriting and rating methods – including drivers and levers of profitable growth;
Intermediate to Advanced SAS and/or SQL;
Intermediate to Advanced PowerBI, Excel, R and/or Python and, more generally, of the broader MS Office suite;
Prior experience on Google Cloud Platform and IBM Cognos TM1 is advantageous although not essential;
A “can do”, team focused attitude with the ability to work autonomously while maintaining focus.


Our perks
Location – Our office is conveniently based in Toowong Village shopping centre - a city fringe location with access to retail, restaurants, various parking options and public transport.
Extra leave - Enjoy additional leave days on us! You’ll receive a paid ‘ME’ day and one paid volunteer leave day annually. Team members can also purchase up to two additional weeks of leave per year.
Paid parental leave - We support our new parents with paid parental leave and other benefits.
Workplace giving - If you’re passionate about a cause, then we are too – we offer workplace giving and we’ll dollar match your donations to registered charities.
Development opportunities - We’re championing your development with internal programs and access to a wide range of online courses.
Employee discounts - You’ll receive discounts on Budget Direct insurance products.
Reward and recognition - We reward high performance with employee recognition, reward and incentive schemes.
Onsite facilities - There’s excellent end-of-trip facilities on offer and private spaces for nursing mothers.
Get social - Join our vibrant social and community activities including annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events across each of our sites



