About BHP

At BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential. With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success.

Come and be a part of this success.

About the Role
BHP’s Performance and Improvement group was established to identify, maximise and implement value-adding and performance improvement opportunities across the value chain of BHP’s assets.

The Value Analytics team, as part of this group, is a collaborative team of simulation specialists, data analysts and data scientists who combine these skill areas to analyse the end to end value chain of BHP’s assets, to identify, evaluate and recommend opportunities to lift asset performance. You will be part of this global team, working alongside other performance and improvement specialists, using the asset data and drawing on the knowledge of operations and business subject matter experts linked with BHPs assets to implement and track the effectiveness of the improvement projects.

This is a Brisbane based role offering a fixed term opportunity working Monday to Friday. Some travel may be required. Flexible working options are available.

In this role, you will:
Uncover areas of value-adding business and performance improvement opportunities across the BHP value chain, and identify and solve the most complex problems in the business;
Work closely with operations and stakeholders to ensure that the relevant business problems are defined, including setting the problem context, understanding the business requirements and success measures, and managing potential challenges;
Develop dynamic discrete-event models to simulate the asset supply chain including mine operations, trucking and rail networks, processing plants and product loading and dispatch using AnyLogic simulation software;
Design dynamic model functionality at a suitable level of detail, ensuring the models are fit for purpose, able to generate and deliver meaningful results and provide actionable insights to the business;
Work collaboratively with site SMEs and the data analysts and data scientists in the Value Analytics team - interrogating and analysing data from large data source records in order to gain insights, understand operational and performance issues and produce input data for the dynamic models;
Define simulation cases, process model results and produce visualisations to support findings and solutions;
Confidently present ideas, results and recommendations to a variety of stakeholders;
Build business partnerships and maintain strong working relationships with key stakeholders across BHP.
About You
Critical requirements: Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics or analytics-related tertiary qualifications, together with a passion for problem solving and using data and simulation to identify, evaluate and support performance improvement initiatives.

Other attributes you may have would include some or all of the following:
Practical experience in mining, minerals processing and resource industries, or equivalent heavy industries, which may include experience in operations or consulting in these areas;
Experience in performance improvement ideation and hypothesis development, including exploring and proposing new ideas that may have benefits for the operation and business;
Strong analytical, critical thinking and creative problem solving skills to generate value through simulation, while maintaining a practical and strategic focus;
Capability in project scoping, project planning and executing work using a disciplined approach to attain project goals;
Strong presentation and communication skills, and ability to influence stakeholders within different areas of expertise.

About Our Process

At BHP, we are committed to employing individuals who align with the BHP Charter Values and meet the requirements of the role. As part of the recruitment process, there are a number of checks which may be conducted to demonstrate applicants suitability for a role including police / criminal background checks, medical, drug and alcohol testing, due diligence checks, right to work checks, and/or reference checks.

To ensure the safety and wellbeing of our people, BHP requires employees in Australia to be fully vaccinated against Covid-19 in line with BHP’s Covid Policy and any relevant State health directives. If you are applying for a role at BHP please consider this requirement when submitting your application. BHP will also adhere to any relevant health directives that may be made that affects our workforce.

Supporting a Diverse Workforce
The size and magnitude of our business not only provides significant opportunity for professional development, but also attractive salary packages with performance-based bonuses and a unique BHP employee share program.

At BHP, we recognise that we are strengthened by diversity. We are committed to providing a work environment in which everyone is included, treated fairly and with respect. We are an Equal Opportunity employer and we encourage applications from women and Indigenous people. We know there are many aspects of our employees' lives that are important, and work is only one of these, so we offer benefits to enable your work to fit with your life. These benefits include flexible working options, a generous paid parental leave policy, other extended leave entitlements and parent rooms.

Prensa is a risk management consultancy which services clients throughout Australia. The business has over 250 consultants working out of offices in most Australian states and provides a range of risk management services including health and safety, environment, occupational hygiene, hazardous materials and emergency management. In Queensland, Prensa has diverse range of clients with key clients including Downer Defence, Queensland Department of Main Roads, Brisbane City Council and QBuild.
Prensa prides itself on expediting the development of consultants compared to larger firms, giving its consultants exposure to all aspects of a project, no matter what level of experience you have. The opportunity for growth and development within Prensa is unlimited
Are you?
A forward-thinking, motivated environmental consultant then we are keen to speak with you. To be successful in this role, you will be:

Highly motivated and have the ability to engage with clients one on one;
Driven to progress your career and develop technically;
Rapidly develop into a Team Leader or Managing Consulting Role; and
Confident in your ability to deliver innovative solutions and outstanding service to our clients.
What will you do?
The diverse role will focus on consulting in the field of Contaminated Land Management (CLM), including:

Project management;
Fee proposal writing;
Contaminated land and surface water/groundwater assessments;
High profile water quality monitoring programmes, statewide;
Environmental due diligence assessments;
Landfill gas monitoring projects;
Remediation projects;
Development of environmental management plans; and
Have the opportunity to travel to remote sites from time to time to service client projects.
TIn addition, you will work closely with our Occupational Hygiene and HAZMAT staff and an on-site NATA accredited laboratory.
How can I succeed in this role?
To succeed in this role, you should meet the following key skills and requirements:

A tertiary qualification in science, environmental science or engineering;
Between two (2) and five (5) years of professional consulting experience;
An ability to independently write quality technical reports and interpret data;
Good communication skills;
Attention to detail;
Project management skills including engaging subcontractors, managing health and safety requirements and exposure to invoicing;
Be passionate about their job and strive for continuous improvement;
A working knowledge of ESdat, ProUCL and gINT applications;
Experience in GIS and CAD is beneficial;
Australian Citizenship to obtain Defence Clearance is favourable; and
Driver’s licence.
This position provides an excellent opportunity to advance your career in the CLM field in Queensland with an organisation committed to the development of their staff and achieving and celebrating success together.
Performance is rewarded and a work-life balance is encouraged. You will also gain experience from our highly experienced senior technical staff (three SQPs) in a challenging and quality-focused environment. The successful applicant will be provided with a wide range of technical and consulting-based training, will be assigned to an experienced mentor and may be offered the opportunity for interstate travel. Remuneration will be based on experience.
Please forward your resume with a covering letter to recruitment@prensa.com.au
